cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with video interpolation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for video interpolation, which involves exploiting acceleration information in videos. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also involves the development of a flow reversal layer and techniques for flow refinement, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with the temporal limitation of camera sensors, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
